## Webhook Server — Explained

Right now pi is a **CLI tool**. You type in terminal, get response. That's it.

A webhook server wraps pi's SDK into an **HTTP API** so any app can talk to it:

```
Browser / Mobile App / Slack Bot / CI Pipeline
              │
              │  POST /chat { "message": "review this PR" }
              ▼
        Your HTTP Server
              │
              │  createAgentSession() + session.prompt()
              ▼
        Pi Agent (with tools, skills, extensions)
              │
              │  session.subscribe() → streaming events
              ▼
        SSE Stream back to client
```

### What it solves

| Without webhook | With webhook |
|----------------|-------------|
| Pi only works in terminal | Any app can use pi |
| One user at a time | Multiple concurrent users |
| No integration possible | Slack, GitHub Actions, web apps, mobile apps all work |
| Manual process | Automatable |

### Concrete use cases

1. **Web UI** — Build a ChatGPT-like interface for your team
2. **Slack bot** — `/pi review this code` sends to your server
3. **GitHub Actions** — CI calls pi to auto-review PRs
4. **IDE plugin** — VS Code extension talks to local pi server
5. **Mobile app** — Code review on your phone

### The core pattern

```typescript
import express from "express";
import { createAgentSession, SessionManager } from "@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent";

const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

// One session per conversation
const sessions = new Map<string, AgentSession>();

app.post("/chat", async (req, res) => {
  const { sessionId, message } = req.body;

  // Get or create session
  let session = sessions.get(sessionId);
  if (!session) {
    const result = await createAgentSession({
      sessionManager: SessionManager.inMemory(),
    });
    session = result.session;
    sessions.set(sessionId, session);
  }

  // Set up SSE streaming
  res.setHeader("Content-Type", "text/event-stream");
  res.setHeader("Cache-Control", "no-cache");
  res.setHeader("Connection", "keep-alive");

  const unsubscribe = session.subscribe((event) => {
    if (event.type === "message_update") {
      if (event.assistantMessageEvent.type === "text_delta") {
        // Stream each token to client
        res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({ 
          type: "token", 
          text: event.assistantMessageEvent.delta 
        })}\n\n`);
      }
    }
    if (event.type === "agent_end") {
      res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({ type: "done" })}\n\n`);
      res.end();
    }
  });

  // Send prompt to agent
  await session.prompt(message);

  // Cleanup on client disconnect
  req.on("close", () => {
    unsubscribe();
  });
});

// Session management
app.delete("/session/:id", (req, res) => {
  const session = sessions.get(req.params.id);
  session?.dispose();
  sessions.delete(req.params.id);
  res.json({ ok: true });
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Pi API running on http://localhost:3000");
});
