### Key design decisions in the example

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| **SSE** (not WebSocket) | Simpler, works with fetch(), auto-reconnects |
| **In-memory sessions** | Example stays simple, no file I/O |
| **Session per conversation** | Each user/chat gets isolated context |
| **Streaming** | User sees tokens in real-time, not waiting for full response |
| **`/session/:id` DELETE** | Clean up idle sessions, prevent memory leaks |

